/**
  * INJURED PERSON
  */
// This is an injured person behavior. This behavior illustrates the usage of the "exactly 1" selector and
// "slowing down" action. It also shows the behavior using "an" instead of "a".
Consider an injured-person.

// This indicates that a single random person is injured.
Exactly 1 random pedestrian is an injured-person.

// There is only one state for an injured person
An injured-person can be INJURED.

// No state transition rules. The person is injured for the entire simulation.

// What the behaviors mean
An injured-person who is INJURED will walk 5% slower.